        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 8 at 7:34PM CDT until September 8 at 8:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Beaver County in the Panhandle of Oklahoma...
Western Lipscomb County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 830 PM CDT.

* At 734 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southeast
of Elmwood, or 18 miles south of Beaver, moving southeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Booker and Darrouzett.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
